data.title: Alex Orlando - Men's Cross Country
data.meta_description: Alex Orlando - 2010 Outdoor (Redshirt): Came in fourth in his debut in the 3000 meter steeplechase with a time of 9:27.57 at the Swarthmore Last Chance Meet ...
data.text:
2010 Outdoor (Redshirt): Came in fourth in his debut in the 3000 meter steeplechase with a time of 9:27.57 at the Swarthmore Last Chance Meet ... Finished 12th in the 1500 meters (4:02.40) at the Villanova Duals ... Competed unattached.

2010 Indoor: Redshirted.

2009 Cross Country (Redshirt): Finished 21st in the four-mile Main Line Invitational with a time of 22:01.87 ... Returned to the same course later in the season and improved his time to 21:23.66 and a 14th place finish in the JV Meet ... Posted an 8K time of 27:00 in the JV race at the Paul Short Run ... Competed unattached.

Monsignor Farrell: Two-time All-American in the 4xMile relay and the 4x800 meter relay ... Competed twice in the 4x800 Championship of America race at the Penn Relays ... As a senior was a state champion in cross country as well as indoors in the 1600 meters and the 3200 meters.

Personal: Born 3/22/91 ... One of two sons of Justin and Pamela Orlando ... Has a brother, Anthony ... Majoring in Economics.

CAREER HIGHLIGHTS

New York state champion in the 2008 high school cross country meet

Indoor 2009 state champion in the 1600 meters and 3200 meters
